This paper deals with the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) and focuses on edge elimination approaches to speed up the calculation of optimal TSP tours. This involves analyzing the expected number of remaining edges after the edge elimination procedure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) which deals with the design and analysis of efficient algorithms and data structures. The paper also involves the analysis of geometric properties of the input points, which suggests the category cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the expected number of remaining edges, which suggests the category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The TSP is a well-known optimization problem, and the paper proposes approaches to solve it efficiently, which suggests the category cs.NE (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper proposes approaches to speed up the calculation of optimal TSP tours, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of intelligent algorithms to solve complex problems.
